Rule: Higher education levels (Prof-school) lead to higher income.
Marital status changes (from Single to Widowed) can lead to higher income.
Race diversity (being "Other") can lead to higher income.
Consistent work hours (even with fewer hours in some cases) can lead to higher income.
Employment in the Government sector leads to higher income.
Gender remains constant (Male), indicating that other factors (education, marital status, race, work hours, workclass) play a role in changing income predictions.
